The paper deals with canonical correlation analysis (CCA) applied to multi-view data, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). The specific application of the method is for satellite image change detection, which falls under the category of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimization problem used to mitigate the effect of alignment errors, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of context regularization, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multi-view data, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
